  <front>
   <head>The PHOENIX. A SONG.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A Female Friend advis'd a Swain</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">(Whose Heart she wish'd at ease)</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Make Love thy Pleasure, not thy Pain,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Nor let it deeply seize.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Beauty, where Vanities abound,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">No serious Passion claims;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then, 'till a  can be found,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Do not admit the Flames.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But griev'd She finds, that his Replies</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">(Since prepossess'd when Young)</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Take all their Hints from  Eyes,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">None from  Tongue.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thus,  of our Aim we miss,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Who wou'd unbend thy Bow;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And each slight Nymph a  is,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">When Love will have it so.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
